gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString:
High Resolution Layer Imperviousness product at pan-European level captures the spatial distribution of artificially sealed areas including the level of sealing of the soil per area unit.
The product has a three years cycle and is available for the 2006, 2009, 2012, 2015 and 2018 reference years including change layers available for 2006-2009, 2009-2012, 2012-2015, 2015-2018, and in addition a change layer available for 2006-2012 and aligned with the CORINE Land Cover periodicity. For the 2018 reference year the product is complemented with the binary Impervious-Built up product, which also includes the aggregated Share of Built-up product showing the percentage of built-up areas across Europe.
High Resolution Layer Imperviousness product is part of the European Unionâ€™s Copernicus Land Monitoring Service.
